The paper deals with unsupervised text style transfer, which is a problem in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a deep generative model, which involves machine learning techniques such as recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and encoder-decoder models, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The paper also uses probabilistic modeling and variational inference, which are common in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper includes experiments on language translation, which is a common task in cs.CV (Computer Vision).
